(HydraDB++ in an Autonomous AI Agent Loop) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Task intake) Tj
T*
(The agent receives a goal, environment observations, tool outputs, and the current) Tj
T*
(conversation turn. Before acting, it treats the new input as candidate memory, not trusted) Tj
T*
(truth.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Memory defense gate) Tj
T*
(Every candidate fact passes through poisoning defense before long-term storage. Rapid) Tj
T*
(contradictions, gradual drift, and authority-injection patterns are checked first. Safe) Tj
T*
(facts are stored normally, warning-level facts are downgraded, and critical facts are) Tj
T*
(blocked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. Fact and entity extraction) Tj
T*
(The agent extracts structured entities, relations, and facts from the latest interaction.) Tj
T*
(This turns free-form dialogue into graph-ready memory such as user identity, preferences,) Tj
T*
(locations, plans, and task state.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Sentiment capture) Tj
T*
(In parallel, sentiment analysis detects whether the agent learned an opinion, preference, or) Tj
T*
(emotional stance. Strong likes and dislikes become high-salience memory because they) Tj
T*
(strongly affect future responses, recommendations, and planning.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. Commit creation) Tj
T*
(The interaction is saved as a Git-style temporal commit. This gives the agent an append-only) Tj
T*
(memory timeline instead of mutable state, which helps with traceability, rollback, and) Tj
T*
(debugging.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. Hybrid storage) Tj
T*
(The same interaction is stored in three retrieval forms:) Tj
T*
(- graph memory for structured facts and relationships) Tj
T*
(- vector memory for semantic retrieval) Tj
T*
(- sparse keyword memory for exact or BM25-style matching) Tj
T*
(This lets the agent answer both precise factual questions and fuzzy semantic questions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7. Background pruning) Tj
T*
(As memory grows, pruning scores retention value using salience, recency decay, and) Tj
T*
(reinforcement from access history. Important memories remain HOT, secondary ones become) Tj
T*
(WARM, and stale low-value ones become COLD or archived. The agent keeps long-term memory) Tj
T*
(without drowning in noise.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(8. Planning step) Tj
T*
(When the autonomous agent is about to act, it retrieves relevant memory for the current) Tj
T*
(subgoal. Query expansion creates multiple search variants. Retrieval fuses vector hits,) Tj
ET
endstream
