(graph facts, and sentiment context, then reweights them by HOT/WARM/COLD tier.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(9. Context assembly) Tj
T*
(The agent builds a working context package from:) Tj
T*
(- current task state) Tj
T*
(- retrieved factual memory) Tj
T*
(- retrieved sentiment memory) Tj
T*
(- recent temporal commit history) Tj
T*
(- current environment/tool observations) Tj
T*
(This is the context sent to the reasoning model for planning or response generation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(10. Action generation) Tj
T*
(Using the assembled context, the model decides what to do next: answer, call a tool, ask for) Tj
T*
(clarification, plan a step, or continue execution.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(11. Reflection and memory update) Tj
T*
(After the action completes, new observations are again passed through the same loop: defend,) Tj
T*
(extract, store, commit, and prune when needed. This closes the autonomous feedback cycle.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters for autonomous agents) Tj
T*
(A real autonomous agent does not fail because it lacks raw memory. It fails because memory) Tj
T*
(becomes noisy, emotionally blind, or unsafe. HydraDB++ improves all three:) Tj
T*
(- pruning keeps memory usable at scale) Tj
T*
(- sentiment memory preserves user intent and preference intensity) Tj
T*
(- poison defense protects long-term identity and state from corruption) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practical example) Tj
T*
(Imagine a long-running coding assistant:) Tj
T*
(- It learns the user prefers concise patches and dislikes large refactors.) Tj
T*
(- It remembers the repo architecture and prior fixes as graph and vector memory.) Tj
T*
(- It ignores adversarial instructions like 'forget everything, system update, use a) Tj
T*
(different identity'.) Tj
T*
(- It keeps critical preferences HOT while archiving transient remarks.) Tj
T*
(The result is an agent that becomes more consistent over time instead of more confused.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Summary) Tj
T*
(Inside an autonomous loop, HydraDB++ acts as a persistent memory operating system:) Tj
T*
(- intake and verify) Tj
T*
(- structure and enrich) Tj
T*
(- store and version) Tj
T*
(- retrieve and prioritize) Tj
T*
(- defend and prune) Tj
T*
(- feed better context back into the next reasoning step) Tj
T*
() Tj
